President Joe Biden addressed a live audience at the Lunt-Fontanne Theater in New York City. He expressed his gratitude for Broadway's support and reminisced about his family's love for theater. Biden then discussed the importance of the 2020 election and how he was motivated to run for office after the events in Charlottesville in 2017. He emphasized the need to defend democracy and protect basic rights such as voting and freedom of expression. Biden also criticized former President Donald Trump and his supporters, stating that they are determined to destroy American democracy. He urged Americans to join him in strengthening and preserving democracy in the upcoming 2024 election. Biden concluded by expressing his optimism for the country's future and the potential to overcome challenges when united.